<p><b>Steven Frank Albini</b> (born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1962-07-22"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="07-22"><a href="/wiki/July_22" title="July 22">July 22</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1962" title="1962">1962</a></span>) is an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Audio_engineer" title="Audio engineer" class="mw-redirect">audio engineer</a>, singer, songwriter, <a href="/wiki/Guitarist" title="Guitarist">guitarist</a>, and music journalist. He was a member of <a href="/wiki/Big_Black" title="Big Black">Big Black</a>, <a href="/wiki/Rapeman" title="Rapeman">Rapeman</a> and <a href="/wiki/Flour_(band)" title="Flour (band)">Flour</a>, and is currently a member of <a href="/wiki/Shellac_(band)" title="Shellac (band)">Shellac</a>. He is founder, owner, and <a href="/wiki/Audio_engineering" title="Audio engineering">engineer</a> of <a href="/wiki/Electrical_Audio" title="Electrical Audio">Electrical Audio</a>, a <a href="/wiki/Recording_studio" title="Recording studio">recording studio</a> complex located in <a href="/wiki/Chicago,_Illinois" title="Chicago, Illinois" class="mw-redirect">Chicago</a>.</p>
